<subSubSection pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,1144,1999]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1144,1171]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
8.4−9.8 mm long; slender body; with dingy orange pronotum having median dark markings, and medi- um brown elytra with narrowly paler interstitial lines 1, 2 and suture. Dorsally reflexed lateral margins of 
<date box="[1324,1358,1181,1207]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V7</date>
enfold sides of T8. Belongs to that section of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[594,729,1217,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[594,729,1217,1243]" italics="true" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where neither 
<date box="[901,935,1217,1243]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V7</date>
nor T8 are prolonged and apically inclined. Known only from the 
<collectingCountry box="[400,530,1253,1279]" name="Philippines" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="133" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="131.[151,1437,1144,1999]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,433,1288,1315]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Description of male</emphasis>
. 8.4−9.8 mm long; 3.2 mm wide. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[910,1072,1288,1315]" captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Figs 405−409</figureCitation>
): (the specimens were originally preserved in 70% ethanol and remounted). Pronotum yellowish brown with paired median areas beside midline darker (
<typeStatus box="[239,339,1361,1387]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">holotype</typeStatus>
male 
<figureCitation box="[411,510,1361,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 409</figureCitation>
); or dingy brown with mid to dark brown markings beside mid line not reaching the narrowly pale posterior margin, and anterolateral and posterolateral corners paler dingy brown, and median line widely paler yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[501,661,1432,1459]" captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Figs 405, 408</figureCitation>
); MN and MS paler than pronotum, pale cream to pale dingy brown; elytra medium brown with interstitial lines 1, 2 and suture narrowly paler brown; elytral punctation black; head antennae and labrum very dark brown; ventral aspect pro and mesothorax brown, of metathorax dark brown; all legs with basal segments light brown, tibiae and tarsi 1 mid brown; legs 2 light brown except for darker brown tarsi; all of legs 3 light brown; basal abdominal ventrites brown, 
<date box="[774,808,1577,1603]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V6</date>
very dark brown, LO creamy yellow; basal tergites pale brown, T7, 8 pale yellowish. Pronotum: narrower than humeral width. Elytron: subparallel sided. Abdomen (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Figs 406, 410−412</figureCitation>
): LO entire in both 
<date box="[535,639,1649,1675]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V6 and 7</date>
occupying all of 
<date box="[838,872,1649,1675]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V6</date>
and extending to sides and into MPP of 
<date box="[1332,1368,1649,1675]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V7</date>
; MPP narrow and apically acute, not inclined dorsally; dorsally reflexed margins of 
<date box="[1034,1068,1685,1711]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V7</date>
enfold the sides of the posterior portion of T8 (
<figureCitation box="[322,417,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 411</figureCitation>
arrowed). T8 (
<figureCitation box="[591,693,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Fig. 412</figureCitation>
): about half as wide as 
<date box="[966,1002,1721,1747]" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">V7</date>
, subparallel sided with posterior margin straight (depending on orientation this margin may appear emarginated); anterolateral arms narrowed, slightly expanded in vertical plane and shorter than posterior entire portion; without ventrally directed pieces arising from bases of anterolateral arms. Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[665,826,1829,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Figs 416, 417</figureCitation>
): with elongate very slender anterior portion of sheath sternite; anterior margin of dorsal portion of sheath tergite gently emarginated. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1349,1864,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 405−417" captionStartId="132.[151,264,1885,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,166,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@132.[216,1372,166,1865]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURES 405−417. Pygoluciola matalangao sp. nov. type males. 405 habitus dorsal; 406 habitus ventral; 407 head anterior; 408, 409 dorsal pronotum; 410 abdomen ventral tergite 8 removed; 411 terminal abdominal segments dorsal, tergite 8 removed (arrows indicate dorsally reflexed margins of ventrite 7); 412 tergite 8 ventral; 413−415 aedeagus: 413 ventral; 414 left lateral; 415 dorsal; 416, 417 aedeagal sheath: 416 dorsal; 417 ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508254" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508254/files/figure.png" pageId="131" pageNumber="132">Figs 413−415</figureCitation>
): apical portion of LL membranous and extending well beyond acute apex of ML with margins clothed with a single line of hairs; basal sclerotised portion of LL separated along half its dorsal length; anterior dorsal basal margin of LL irregularly prolonged to the left, and rounded.
</paragraph>
